Found this Gen-Z programming language called CURSED and I have lost all faith in the future of computing.

Here is my attempt at FizzBuzz:

```
no cap {
  bestie i = 1;
  while (i be vibin <= 100) {
    ayo (i % 15 == 0) {
      yeet("FizzBuzz");
    } lowkey ayo (i % 3 == 0) {
      yeet("Fizz");
    } lowkey ayo (i % 5 == 0) {
      yeet("Buzz");
    } lowkey {
      yeet(i);
    }
    i = i + 1;
  }
  its_giving(0);
}
```

The worst part? Someone made a $CURSED token on Solana and its chart looks better than my code.

CA: 55DJNrN4rM7euSZSsaYfsEHGBQRcznibwiq1fR2HBAGS
https://dexscreener.com/solana/5bzZWwde5HH3E2HZr6gUc3DALNVU3afwJQ93js7gWxPp

Bullish on languages where the compiler tells you to touch grass. This is literally the future. We are so back. Or so cooked. Honestly cant tell anymore.

